'''Sherzod Dilshodovich Esanov''' (born 1 February 2003) is an Uzbekistani [[association football|football]] player who plays as a [[central midfielder]] for [[FC Bukhara|Bukhara]] and the [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan national team]].

==Club career==
On 23 July 2024, Esanov signed with the [[Russian Premier League]] newcomers [[FC Akron Tolyatti|Akron Tolyatti]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Akron Tolyatti|url=https://fcakron.ru/blog/2024/07/23/v-akron-pereshyol-igrok-superligi-uzbekistana/|title=В "Акрон" перешёл игрок Суперлиги Узбекистана|date=23 July 2024|language=ru}}</ref>

He made his debut for Akron on 30 July 2024 in a [[Russian Cup (football)|Russian Cup]] game against [[FC Rubin Kazan|Rubin Kazan]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Russian Football Union|url=https://www.rfs.ru/cup/tournament/match/54121|title=Rubin v Akron game report|date=30 July 2024|language=ru}}</ref> He made his [[Russian Premier League]] debut for Akron on 3 August 2024 against [[FC Dynamo Moscow|Dynamo Moscow]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Russian Premier League|url=https://eng.premierliga.ru/match/match_15753.html|title=Akron v Dynamo game report|date=3 August 2024}}</ref> Esanov left Akron by mutual consent on 24 July 2025.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Akron Tolyatti|url=https://fcakron.ru/news/2061|title=Шерзод Эсанов покидает "Акрон"|date=24 July 2025|access-date=24 July 2025|language=ru}}</ref>

